	)
	(text "Power Pins\n5V - This is 5v out from the USB port. You can also use this as a voltage input but you must have \nsome sort of diode (schottky, signal, power) between your external power source and this pin with \nanode to battery, cathode to 5V pin.\n3V3 - This is the regulated output from the onboard regulator. You can draw 700mA\nGND - Power/data/signal ground\nStrapping Pins\nAccording to the chip manual of ESP32C3, GPIO2, GPIO8 and GPIO9 in the chip are Strapping Pins, the\n high and low level configurations of these pins may allow the chip to enter into different Boot modes, \nplease pay attention to this point when you use these pins, otherwise it may prevent your XIAO from \nuploading or executing the program all the time."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 297.18 101.854 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 0.635 0.635)
			)
		)
		(uuid "2c6a9304-f270-4c3c-b3f7-89a825f67559")
	)
